[SN]TITLE[SN]
Glamorgan's final pre-season friendly ends in draw

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
Glamorgan completed their pre-season preparations with a drawn friendly against Nottinghamshire in Cardiff.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
Batsman Nick Selman (97) and spinner Andrew Salter (four for 47) were the leading performers as both sides batted twice in the two-day game.
Glamorgan begin their county championship season on Friday, 7 April at Northamptonshire.
The Welsh county have fitness fears of Timm van der Gugten, Graham Wagg and Will Bragg.
